{
  "stem": "25114.7",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't the right thing to do, but at this moment it seems right, because we had to go through very bad-- bad-- pass-- while the others who went later went out just what-- on certain trains, and they came right-- [LAUGHS] so they did the same.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But at this time, it was necessary for a for few reasons.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So [? we'll ?]-- so we decided to leave, and we left.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in the meantime, you want to know about my family-- what happened.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My sister survived before I escaped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my husband says he'll come and get them back to the partisan-- it became impossible.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because after they found out that people are escaping, they put more fences-- another wall and thing-- and getting in and out of ghettos become very, very hard.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Much harder.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were trying even to put the arm-- the rescue to the ghetto-- attack the partisans.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we talked it over at meetings, but nothing came out of it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We thought we-- the odds were too small to attack the ghetto and liberate without everybody getting killed in the process.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they abandoned it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So my sisters were in the ghetto, still.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they were in the ghetto till May-- I think it was May-- till May, '43, when another Aussiedlung took place.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Out of the 500 who were left, [INAUDIBLE] a half of them [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] went in the second aktion.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My sister stayed, only because the-- the-- in the last minute the-- the [? demands ?]-- man-- the German in charge-- came running and said, [NON-ENGLISH]-- he-- he-- pulled her out, and she pulled out my sister.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because their wives told him not to kill her.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because they wanted their dresses.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
